<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A comment was given by Absor about this specifically. (Not bears, but Druids killing animals) It was his idea, that so long as none of the animal was put to waste, from an Environmentalist perspective, it made sense. The whole "Circle of Life" thing. That Druids needed to survive too, just like a bear might kill a rabbit (Where does that foraged rabbit meat come from anyway? I have yet to see one...although Monty Python tells us thats a good thing) in order to survive, we do to (Skin for clothing, tents when we camp, Meat for eating...so on) I happen to be a BIG Roleplayer, and the way I see it, my character HAD to become both a tailor and a baker in order to use the animal parts. Made me popular back in Greater Faydark when I handed out free clothing and food to the "little ones."<P>Just my humble opinion...<P>Kandaen Wolvenfury<BR>29th Level<BR>Innoruuk Server<P>--------------------<P>Kandaen Wolvenfury<BR>30th Level Druid<BR>Innoruuk Server
