There's a very good reason the Romans and Christians don't have accurate records.<BR>Ancient Celtic Druids..definitely not into christianity!<BR>Ancient French Druids.. burned for being witches.<BR>Druids were and are one with the land they protect and nurture. They help attain and keep a healthy BALANCE.. we are not good aligned nor are we evil we stand in between to be sure that the two sides don't disturb mother earth. We understand the animals for they live closely with nature also and protecting those that can not protect themselves is very common for a druid to do. The bears and wolves are pack and family oriented animals that commune with us during our times with nature therefore there is a kinship that developes between the druids and their four footed furry pals. A sick or gravely hurt animal should be sent back to Tunare so that the mothers embrace can comfort the spirit but the bears than roam the hills are free spirits that should be viewed as brothers and sisters. <BR>Verant designed their own version of Druid and unfortunately warped it quite a bit so the few who do follow the druidic faiths cringe but tolerate the interpretation we are forced to swallow.<BR>I have only found one aspect of the EQ druids that really irks me, teleportation.<BR>Where the hell did they come up with this? Druids have always been known to walk with the animals not fly. Transportation required two things.. your feet! In fact druids normally would not evan use a beast of burden but would walk along side their animal friends. Was the druid class so pathetic before teleports that they needed to add this to make them appealing? I wish sometimes I had never evan bought the spells.<P>--------------------<P>Jayde <BR>Dammiana druid of 46 seasons of growth
